WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:06.000
Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:00:17.377 --> 00:00:20.255
<i>[Episode 6]</i>
You know these cleaners...

3
00:00:20.255 --> 00:00:23.912
The image of them eating meals with us?

4
00:00:23.912 --> 00:00:25.031
Fine!

5
00:00:25.031 --> 00:00:29.253
I don't think it's right to
discriminate either.

6
00:00:29.253 --> 00:00:30.513
- But, you know...
- Yes?

7
00:00:30.513 --> 00:00:32.424
It's only hard at the beginning.

8
00:00:32.424 --> 00:00:35.365
Once you allow just one thing...

9
00:00:35.365 --> 00:00:37.893
there are so many problems that follow.

10
00:00:37.893 --> 00:00:40.165
You are correct... so right.

11
00:00:40.165 --> 00:00:42.744
Have a drink. Have a drink.

12
00:00:42.744 --> 00:00:45.906
Will they be satisfied with
eating meals there?

13
00:00:45.906 --> 00:00:47.275
- CEO Min.
- Yes?

14
00:00:47.275 --> 00:00:48.412
You know how it is.

15
00:00:48.412 --> 00:00:53.994
They'll ask for days off, bonuses,
break rooms, this, and that.

16
00:00:53.994 --> 00:00:58.893
They'll make requests for all of that
and it'll be such a pain for me.

17
00:00:58.893 --> 00:01:02.466
We can't allow that to happen.
That cannot happen.

18
00:01:04.449 --> 00:01:06.728
So, CEO Min.

19
00:01:06.728 --> 00:01:09.650
You need to hire the right
people to begin with.

20
00:01:09.650 --> 00:01:13.951
What if young people get together
and form a labor union?

21
00:01:17.008 --> 00:01:18.618
Ah, yes.

22
00:01:22.395 --> 00:01:23.895
<i>I love you.</i>

23
00:01:37.275 --> 00:01:38.532
I love you.

24
00:02:16.768 --> 00:02:17.783
Joon.

25
00:02:19.140 --> 00:02:21.700
You... why are you here?

26
00:02:21.700 --> 00:02:23.962
How? Why? Why? Why?

27
00:02:23.962 --> 00:02:25.875
Don't you remember last night?

28
00:02:27.605 --> 00:02:28.765
Last night?

29
00:02:33.275 --> 00:02:35.955
You need to take
responsibility for me now.

30
00:02:35.955 --> 00:02:38.630
Why do I have to do that?
Why do I have to take responsibility?

31
00:02:38.630 --> 00:02:41.162
What... what did I do?

32
00:02:41.162 --> 00:02:43.272
Don't you remember
what you said to me last night?

33
00:02:44.671 --> 00:02:45.788
What did I say?

34
00:02:48.189 --> 00:02:50.920
Beep, beep, beep, beep.
Beep, beep, beep, beep.

35
00:02:50.920 --> 00:02:52.044
What is that?

36
00:02:52.044 --> 00:02:53.663
Come on now.

37
00:02:53.663 --> 00:02:55.363
You know.

38
00:02:55.363 --> 00:02:57.480
- I don't know.
- Beep, beep, beep, beep.

39
00:02:57.480 --> 00:03:03.773
Beep, beep, beep, beep.
Beep, beep, beep, beep.

40
00:03:06.236 --> 00:03:07.982
This isn't right.

41
00:03:15.433 --> 00:03:16.758
No.

42
00:03:20.980 --> 00:03:23.533
Get away. Get away!

43
00:03:41.914 --> 00:03:44.867
Seriously, I don't know.

44
00:03:56.753 --> 00:03:58.026
I'm going insane.

45
00:04:04.546 --> 00:04:06.902
Oh, I must be crazy!

46
00:04:30.296 --> 00:04:32.859
<i>I love you. I love you. I love you.</i>

47
00:04:32.859 --> 00:04:34.686
Ah, I'm crazy. I'm crazy.

48
00:04:53.483 --> 00:04:54.542
Joon!

49
00:04:55.688 --> 00:04:57.892
What are you doing here?

50
00:04:57.892 --> 00:04:59.659
You slept in so I came to wake you.

51
00:04:59.659 --> 00:05:01.322
That's what I'm saying.

52
00:05:01.322 --> 00:05:03.152
What?

53
00:05:03.152 --> 00:05:05.253
Well, you know.

54
00:05:05.253 --> 00:05:07.162
I don't know. I'm late.

55
00:05:11.101 --> 00:05:12.522
Wait for me!

56
00:05:13.378 --> 00:05:16.229
I'm crazy, so crazy.

57
00:05:26.765 --> 00:05:28.133
I don't know.

58
00:05:29.940 --> 00:05:31.897
Joon!

59
00:05:31.897 --> 00:05:33.046
What's with her?

60
00:05:33.046 --> 00:05:34.346
Must be because she's late.

61
00:05:34.346 --> 00:05:35.541
These are yours.

62
00:05:39.808 --> 00:05:41.484
Get it together.

63
00:05:43.162 --> 00:05:45.008
Joon, wait for me!

64
00:05:59.649 --> 00:06:01.212
- Joon.
- Huh?

65
00:06:01.212 --> 00:06:04.483
Are you sick or something?
You don't look so good.

66
00:06:04.483 --> 00:06:06.645
Ah, no. It's nothing.

67
00:06:11.662 --> 00:06:12.834
Sorry.

68
00:06:14.359 --> 00:06:15.626
Is it a cold?

69
00:06:20.678 --> 00:06:22.953
Gosh, drive carefully.

70
00:06:59.695 --> 00:07:01.750
- Hold on, Joon.
- Huh?

71
00:07:06.183 --> 00:07:08.866
What.. what are you doing?

72
00:07:14.628 --> 00:07:16.743
I think you have a fever.

73
00:07:16.743 --> 00:07:17.780
A fever?

74
00:07:20.707 --> 00:07:22.945
I'm totally okay.

75
00:07:24.770 --> 00:07:26.825
Oh, we're here.
Let's get out.

76
00:07:29.373 --> 00:07:32.255
What a terrible driver!

77
00:07:34.246 --> 00:07:35.349
Joon.

78
00:07:36.495 --> 00:07:37.630
Why aren't they here?

79
00:07:39.162 --> 00:07:40.674
Someone's here, someone's here.

80
00:07:45.969 --> 00:07:48.969
Why is that guy here?

81
00:07:48.969 --> 00:07:51.198
He isn't the CEO
of this cleaning company, is he?

82
00:07:54.388 --> 00:07:59.289
I heard from the section chief that
an unfortunate event occurred yesterday.

83
00:07:59.289 --> 00:08:04.553
When one or two muddy the waters and
our clients start to become unhappy

84
00:08:04.553 --> 00:08:06.762
they will not re-sign
their contract with us.

85
00:08:13.717 --> 00:08:16.688
Hey, why do you have come
into the same one as me?

86
00:08:16.688 --> 00:08:18.698
Are you all right?
You don't look so well.

87
00:08:18.698 --> 00:08:22.356
<i>How could you all protest
in front of the company employees?</i>

88
00:08:22.356 --> 00:08:25.667
What if your actions cause
Gangsu Group to terminate the contract?

89
00:08:25.667 --> 00:08:28.267
That means all of you
here will get fired.

90
00:08:28.267 --> 00:08:30.396
It will only cause pain for all of you.

91
00:08:32.038 --> 00:08:34.518
I won't make this long.

92
00:08:34.518 --> 00:08:38.047
Who is the person
who caused the problem yesterday?

93
00:08:38.047 --> 00:08:39.169
Step forward.

94
00:08:44.414 --> 00:08:46.610
I want the leader to come out!

95
00:08:50.813 --> 00:08:52.553
We're sorry we're late.

96
00:08:53.552 --> 00:08:54.632
What do we do?

97
00:08:58.933 --> 00:09:00.062
Wait.

98
00:09:01.632 --> 00:09:02.922
What's with you two?

99
00:09:04.273 --> 00:09:05.384
You...

100
00:09:10.702 --> 00:09:13.395
They are the ones who didn't
know their place yesterday.

101
00:09:19.164 --> 00:09:23.034
What? The chairman's second son?

102
00:09:23.034 --> 00:09:25.472
What is the meaning of this?

103
00:09:25.472 --> 00:09:30.212
Is this a test from Gangsu Group with
the upcoming contract renewal?

104
00:09:30.212 --> 00:09:33.053
Well, I never received any such orders.

105
00:09:35.683 --> 00:09:37.323
What's going on?

106
00:09:37.323 --> 00:09:39.054
Oh, Chief!

107
00:09:39.054 --> 00:09:42.005
I'm glad you're here.

108
00:09:42.005 --> 00:09:43.183
What's the problem?

109
00:09:43.183 --> 00:09:47.203
Ah, well to be honest...

110
00:09:47.203 --> 00:09:48.823
I should've introduced myself earlier.

111
00:09:48.823 --> 00:09:51.223
I am CEO Min Sang Ho
of Hangang Services.

112
00:09:53.343 --> 00:09:55.405
Yes. It's an honor.

113
00:09:58.340 --> 00:10:01.645
The thing is, Sir...

114
00:10:04.605 --> 00:10:07.953
Don't worry about it
too much. Go on as usual.

115
00:10:07.953 --> 00:10:09.577
Yes, I will.

116
00:10:09.577 --> 00:10:14.145
Regarding any issues
caused by Mister Byun Hyuk

117
00:10:14.145 --> 00:10:17.198
I'll do what I can to handle
the public opinion.

118
00:10:17.198 --> 00:10:18.938
All you need to do is say the word.

119
00:10:18.938 --> 00:10:21.366
What do you mean handle public opinion?

120
00:10:21.366 --> 00:10:24.766
Are you implying this
is all a show for the public?

121
00:10:24.766 --> 00:10:27.538
Pardon? Of course, not.

122
00:10:27.538 --> 00:10:29.568
That wasn't my intent at all.

123
00:10:29.568 --> 00:10:31.747
He won't need special
treatment as the employer's son.

124
00:10:31.747 --> 00:10:34.718
Treat Hyuk like any other employee.

125
00:10:34.718 --> 00:10:36.188
The same?

126
00:10:37.167 --> 00:10:39.486
Yes, the same.

127
00:10:39.486 --> 00:10:42.746
The same without any special treatment.

128
00:10:42.746 --> 00:10:46.536
If I hear that he's getting
special "Golden Spoon" treatment

129
00:10:46.536 --> 00:10:49.860
I won't stand for it.

130
00:10:49.860 --> 00:10:51.882
Do you understand my meaning?

131
00:10:51.882 --> 00:10:55.872
Yes, I understand your meaning.

132
00:10:55.872 --> 00:11:00.443
It would be an honor if I could
meet with you another time.

133
00:11:20.958 --> 00:11:22.641
Yeah.

134
00:11:22.641 --> 00:11:26.496
Push, pop, push, pop, push, pop.

135
00:11:27.944 --> 00:11:30.054
Joon, did you see?

136
00:11:30.054 --> 00:11:31.345
Today is all clear!

137
00:11:31.345 --> 00:11:33.025
Flush, flush!

138
00:11:33.025 --> 00:11:34.236
You did well.

139
00:11:35.616 --> 00:11:37.427
Can you come out for a bit?

140
00:11:40.406 --> 00:11:42.386
Gosh, seriously.

141
00:11:46.577 --> 00:11:50.938
Are the facilities managers
doing their jobs or not?

142
00:11:50.938 --> 00:11:53.696
They should figure out
the source of the problem and fix it.

143
00:11:53.696 --> 00:11:56.295
Is it the toilet or the drain?

144
00:11:56.295 --> 00:11:57.693
Don't you agree, Joon?

145
00:11:57.693 --> 00:12:00.026
That's how management usually is.

146
00:12:00.026 --> 00:12:03.198
Rather than taking countermeasures,
they work harder on the aftermath.

147
00:12:04.299 --> 00:12:06.347
That includes your older brother.

148
00:12:07.876 --> 00:12:09.457
Come on, Joon.

149
00:12:09.457 --> 00:12:13.659
Including my brother
in that group is upsetting to me.

150
00:12:13.659 --> 00:12:15.669
My older brother
isn't that kind of person.

151
00:12:15.669 --> 00:12:17.000
You trust your brother that much?

152
00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:19.198
Of course. I may not trust my father.

153
00:12:19.198 --> 00:12:20.579
I can trust my brother though.

154
00:12:20.579 --> 00:12:25.018
Even if everyone turns on me,
he will be on my side until the end.

155
00:12:25.018 --> 00:12:27.385
Yeah? Really?

156
00:12:27.385 --> 00:12:29.196
Of course, really.

157
00:12:33.026 --> 00:12:36.184
That's a relief if it's true.

158
00:12:36.184 --> 00:12:37.881
Joon, Mister Byun.

159
00:12:37.881 --> 00:12:39.215
- Come have some coffee.
- Okay.

160
00:12:39.215 --> 00:12:40.783
- Come on.
- Okay.

161
00:12:45.361 --> 00:12:47.707
Her nuance makes me feel uneasy.

162
00:12:49.428 --> 00:12:50.736
Joon!

163
00:12:57.255 --> 00:12:59.646
What should I do with them?

164
00:12:59.646 --> 00:13:01.304
What are you conflicted about?

165
00:13:01.304 --> 00:13:02.961
He said don't treat them any differently.

166
00:13:02.961 --> 00:13:05.533
Ah, I see. I understand.

167
00:13:05.533 --> 00:13:07.712
I'll fire them all today.

168
00:13:08.792 --> 00:13:12.143
No need to do that and
make things noisy.

169
00:13:12.143 --> 00:13:15.062
- What?
- Make them quit on their own.

170
00:13:16.252 --> 00:13:17.880
You can do that, right?

171
00:13:17.880 --> 00:13:21.980
Ah... yes. I can.

172
00:13:21.980 --> 00:13:23.345
I understand.

173
00:13:30.199 --> 00:13:34.135
Do you have a list of the VJs
who do eating programs?

174
00:13:34.135 --> 00:13:37.145
Yes, about 100.

175
00:13:37.145 --> 00:13:39.574
What about magazine
editors and reporters?

176
00:13:39.574 --> 00:13:41.643
Yes, we're waiting to hear from them.

177
00:13:41.643 --> 00:13:45.068
Oh, it'll resolve itself
if you wait, won't it?

178
00:13:45.068 --> 00:13:48.487
Call them yourself
and check. Hurry it up.

179
00:13:48.487 --> 00:13:50.327
Yes, Section Chief.

180
00:13:50.327 --> 00:13:53.728
We don't have much time until
the event, so be on your toes.

181
00:13:53.728 --> 00:13:55.879
- Yes, I understand.
- Yes.

182
00:13:55.879 --> 00:13:57.148
Also, Section Chief Kwon.

183
00:13:59.029 --> 00:14:00.055
Yes?

184
00:14:00.055 --> 00:14:02.674
For the sampling event of
the new food product...

185
00:14:02.674 --> 00:14:05.704
Section Chief Kwon,
you can plan the entire thing.

186
00:14:08.803 --> 00:14:10.515
Me?

187
00:14:10.515 --> 00:14:12.905
Yes, I'm talking about you.

188
00:14:12.905 --> 00:14:18.886
Take charge and plan
the event so that it's a success.

189
00:14:18.886 --> 00:14:20.755
Yes, I'll work hard.

190
00:14:22.105 --> 00:14:25.279
Don't work hard.

191
00:14:25.279 --> 00:14:27.097
You need to do it well.

192
00:14:39.535 --> 00:14:40.982
<i>[Father] </i>

193
00:14:51.043 --> 00:14:53.688
Yes, Managing Director.
I did as you told me.

194
00:15:01.444 --> 00:15:03.723
<i>[Employee Profile]</i>

195
00:15:06.678 --> 00:15:10.573
<i>[Kwon Jae Hoon]</i>

196
00:15:19.346 --> 00:15:22.636
Oh, Jae Hoon.
Sorry to call when you're busy.

197
00:15:22.636 --> 00:15:24.625
What is it?

198
00:15:24.625 --> 00:15:26.014
Well, the thing is...

199
00:15:32.305 --> 00:15:35.230
I came to see Hyuk, Section Chief Kwon.

200
00:15:35.230 --> 00:15:40.220
I heard he had an odd job here,
so I came to see for myself.

201
00:15:40.220 --> 00:15:42.732
Where is my Hyuk?

202
00:15:42.732 --> 00:15:43.740
Hm?

203
00:15:48.110 --> 00:15:49.625
Where is he?

204
00:16:04.962 --> 00:16:06.549
What is this?

205
00:16:06.549 --> 00:16:08.860
Why are we suddenly in charge of this?

206
00:16:08.860 --> 00:16:12.029
People's jobs can change
depending on the situation.

207
00:16:12.029 --> 00:16:14.289
Why are you arguing about it?

208
00:16:14.289 --> 00:16:16.559
Did CEO Min tell you to do this?

209
00:16:19.448 --> 00:16:23.367
Well, who told you to go
eat in the employee cafeteria?

210
00:16:24.682 --> 00:16:28.827
You're telling me this is
because we ate in the cafeteria?

211
00:16:28.827 --> 00:16:31.712
So, is CEO Min is giving us
a taste of our own medicine?

212
00:16:31.712 --> 00:16:32.946
Forget it.

213
00:16:32.946 --> 00:16:35.904
You are all in charge
of this today, so just know that.

214
00:16:35.904 --> 00:16:38.834
It's no fun if you walk off on the job.

215
00:16:38.834 --> 00:16:41.066
You know the terms
of your contract very well.

216
00:16:41.066 --> 00:16:43.140
So, you shouldn't need
much explanation, right?

217
00:16:45.217 --> 00:16:47.106
That guy...

218
00:16:47.106 --> 00:16:50.651
What is so wrong
about eating in the cafeteria?

219
00:16:50.651 --> 00:16:52.697
Does this make sense?

220
00:16:52.697 --> 00:16:55.606
Seems like this is about Mister Byun.

221
00:16:55.606 --> 00:16:58.555
He's getting revenge
for the brick on his head, right?

222
00:16:58.555 --> 00:17:02.122
Still, he is the chairman's
son. I doubt it.

223
00:17:02.122 --> 00:17:04.235
My goodness.

224
00:17:04.235 --> 00:17:06.653
By the way, where is Mister Byun?

225
00:17:06.653 --> 00:17:09.704
You're right.
They took him somewhere else.

226
00:17:09.704 --> 00:17:11.214
I don't see him at all.

227
00:17:13.996 --> 00:17:19.064
What? Mister... Mister Byun Hyuk?

228
00:17:19.064 --> 00:17:21.985
Yes, his mother is looking for him.

229
00:17:21.985 --> 00:17:23.566
Where is Hyuk now?

230
00:17:26.450 --> 00:17:29.215
Ah, wait... wait... wait a moment.

231
00:17:32.555 --> 00:17:35.110
Yes, Manager Jung.
It's me, Section Chief Gong.

232
00:17:35.110 --> 00:17:37.617
Yes, about Mister... Mister Byun Hyuk.

233
00:17:37.617 --> 00:17:40.400
Yes, yes. The chairman's second son.

234
00:17:40.400 --> 00:17:42.891
Can you get him over here now?

235
00:17:42.891 --> 00:17:44.700
Oh, about that...

236
00:17:44.700 --> 00:17:49.112
I received orders that I shouldn't treat
him special as the employer's son.

237
00:17:49.112 --> 00:17:50.882
Where is he right now?

238
00:17:52.999 --> 00:17:54.805
What? What did you say?

239
00:17:54.805 --> 00:17:56.865
Where?

240
00:18:01.284 --> 00:18:02.787
Ah... ah.

241
00:18:20.778 --> 00:18:22.980
What is it? Section Chief Gong!

242
00:18:25.525 --> 00:18:28.246
What... what are we to do?

243
00:18:31.474 --> 00:18:32.515
What?

244
00:18:55.296 --> 00:18:57.861
<i>Oh, Mom!</i>

245
00:18:57.861 --> 00:19:00.752
Oh... oh my, oh my, oh my!

246
00:19:01.919 --> 00:19:04.583
Oh my, oh my, oh my!

247
00:19:04.583 --> 00:19:05.919
Hyuk!

248
00:19:05.919 --> 00:19:09.464
Oh my, oh my! Oh my, hey. Oh my!

249
00:19:09.464 --> 00:19:10.507
Get down.

250
00:19:10.507 --> 00:19:12.785
Mom, I'm flying.

251
00:19:12.785 --> 00:19:15.052
No, no. Don't do that. Get down.

252
00:19:15.052 --> 00:19:16.394
Oh no! No!

253
00:19:16.394 --> 00:19:18.243
Hey!

254
00:19:18.243 --> 00:19:21.071
No, no Hyuk! Get down. Get down!

255
00:19:21.071 --> 00:19:24.147
No, no! You can't do that! No!

256
00:19:24.147 --> 00:19:26.739
Stop that. Stop that and come down!

257
00:19:29.092 --> 00:19:30.457
Honey!

258
00:19:31.552 --> 00:19:34.112
Honey, honey, honey!

259
00:19:35.975 --> 00:19:38.438
What brings you here?

260
00:19:38.438 --> 00:19:40.112
What do you mean?

261
00:19:40.112 --> 00:19:42.912
How could say such a thing like
nothing's going on?

262
00:19:42.912 --> 00:19:47.352
Are you this calm knowing what our
Hyuk is doing right now?

263
