I'm just frustrated seeing you like this.

524
00:38:07.113 --> 00:38:09.966
Why suffer instead of going down
an easier, more comfortable path?

525
00:38:09.966 --> 00:38:11.857
What's an easy and comfortable path?

526
00:38:13.835 --> 00:38:17.694
A career that you can
show off to others about?

527
00:38:17.694 --> 00:38:21.674
Or a high salary?

528
00:38:21.674 --> 00:38:23.413
Ask other people.

529
00:38:23.413 --> 00:38:26.379
Ask them which of us is right.

530
00:38:26.379 --> 00:38:29.629
Don't be delusional that you're right.

531
00:38:29.629 --> 00:38:34.109
In the end, people live
according to their beliefs.

532
00:38:36.627 --> 00:38:38.803
You continue to choose
to work hard labor jobs.

533
00:38:38.803 --> 00:38:41.964
What are these beliefs of yours?

534
00:38:48.060 --> 00:38:49.540
Get going.

535
00:38:50.728 --> 00:38:52.178
I want to rest.

536
00:39:18.212 --> 00:39:20.214
<i>[Employee Application]</i>

537
00:39:57.312 --> 00:39:58.437
Hyuk.

538
00:40:04.663 --> 00:40:07.328
What are you doing here alone?

539
00:40:07.328 --> 00:40:08.696
Nothing really.

540
00:40:10.116 --> 00:40:12.897
How about you? How are you feeling?

541
00:40:14.196 --> 00:40:15.355
I'm all right.

542
00:40:16.814 --> 00:40:19.805
I went to the ER for a cold.

543
00:40:19.805 --> 00:40:20.866
How embarrassing.

544
00:40:20.866 --> 00:40:25.451
It wasn't just a cold.
You had overexerted yourself too.

545
00:40:25.451 --> 00:40:27.712
A cold and overexertion.

546
00:40:27.712 --> 00:40:31.692
And you were down in the garbage
room working where the air was bad.

547
00:40:33.277 --> 00:40:34.511
If you think about it...

548
00:40:37.113 --> 00:40:38.721
it's all my fault.

549
00:40:38.721 --> 00:40:41.913
Hey, why is that your fault?

550
00:40:41.913 --> 00:40:45.152
It's CEO Min's fault
for abusing his power.

551
00:40:45.152 --> 00:40:47.129
Anyway, that makes it my fault.

552
00:40:47.129 --> 00:40:49.752
- Hyuk.
- So, I was thinking, Joon...

553
00:40:49.752 --> 00:40:51.172
I think that...

554
00:40:52.676 --> 00:40:54.411
I should quit.

555
00:40:57.118 --> 00:40:59.252
What are you talking about?

556
00:40:59.252 --> 00:41:02.183
You said we shouldn't quit.
You said so yourself.

557
00:41:02.183 --> 00:41:04.212
You said that it would be shameful.

558
00:41:04.212 --> 00:41:05.859
That it was giving in to injustice.

559
00:41:05.859 --> 00:41:11.277
If I quit, you, Mister Kim,
Mister Lee, and Madam Ahn...

560
00:41:12.609 --> 00:41:14.680
they will all be okay, so...

561
00:41:14.680 --> 00:41:17.078
What about your promise to your father?

562
00:41:17.078 --> 00:41:20.701
He'll assume I can only go that far.

563
00:41:20.701 --> 00:41:23.203
I was always that kind of son.

564
00:41:23.203 --> 00:41:25.142
It won't be anything new for him.

565
00:41:27.181 --> 00:41:28.265
Okay.

566
00:41:32.073 --> 00:41:35.658
Yeah, then quit.

567
00:41:37.915 --> 00:41:41.687
Who can stop you if you
don't want to do it?

568
00:41:41.687 --> 00:41:43.790
However...

569
00:41:43.790 --> 00:41:48.946
don't use me, Mister Kim,
Mister Lee, or Madam Ahn as excuses.

570
00:41:50.587 --> 00:41:54.815
Whether you continue
to work or not, that is your choice.

571
00:41:54.815 --> 00:41:58.901
I don't want to hear
that you did it because of us.

572
00:42:00.567 --> 00:42:04.709
Honestly... it's just an excuse.

573
00:42:06.538 --> 00:42:07.678
Isn't that right?

574
00:42:13.413 --> 00:42:15.808
I told you to get confident on your own.

575
00:42:17.826 --> 00:42:22.667
Claiming your rights is part
of getting confident, Hyuk.

576
00:42:22.667 --> 00:42:24.167
Claiming my rights?

577
00:42:24.167 --> 00:42:28.067
Yes, your rights.

578
00:42:28.067 --> 00:42:31.696
Someone is desperately
hoping that you will give up.

579
00:42:32.770 --> 00:42:34.136
That's what I'm talking about.

580
00:42:36.323 --> 00:42:37.558
<i>For example?</i>

581
00:42:39.495 --> 00:42:42.221
Anything you don't wish
to dirty your hands with.

582
00:42:42.221 --> 00:42:46.750
Something unclear or messy,
anything that's bothersome.

583
00:42:48.325 --> 00:42:52.853
My goodness. It sounds like
you're talking about Hyuk.

584
00:42:52.853 --> 00:42:54.906
It makes me feel awkward to hear it.

585
00:43:14.966 --> 00:43:18.183
Hey... hey.
What's with you suddenly?

586
00:43:23.102 --> 00:43:24.978
I'm just so ashamed.

587
00:43:26.366 --> 00:43:28.509
I'm so ashamed in front of you.

588
00:43:30.940 --> 00:43:33.401
Are you crying?

589
00:43:38.846 --> 00:43:41.174
No need to cry over that.

590
00:43:41.174 --> 00:43:44.685
It's okay, all right? It's okay.

591
00:43:45.777 --> 00:43:47.185
Stop crying.

592
00:43:53.977 --> 00:43:55.292
Gosh.

593
00:43:57.151 --> 00:43:58.359
It's okay.

594
00:44:07.247 --> 00:44:08.792
<i>[Healthy porridge]</i>

595
00:44:32.047 --> 00:44:33.605
Ah, you startled me.

596
00:44:41.727 --> 00:44:42.848
Thank you.

597
00:45:08.388 --> 00:45:11.011
Oh! Hold on.

598
00:45:11.011 --> 00:45:13.232
What? Excuse me!

599
00:45:13.232 --> 00:45:16.047
Excuse me. Excuse me!

600
00:45:16.047 --> 00:45:17.252
My bag.

601
00:45:18.046 --> 00:45:19.098
My bag.

602
00:45:24.779 --> 00:45:27.290
What is it? What?

603
00:45:27.290 --> 00:45:28.460
Who are you?

604
00:45:37.239 --> 00:45:38.272
Bye, then.

605
00:45:46.709 --> 00:45:48.337
What was that?

606
00:45:48.337 --> 00:45:50.410
Oh, that scared me.

607
00:45:50.410 --> 00:45:52.669
Did he move in next door?

608
00:45:52.669 --> 00:45:55.509
Oh, how did he know where I lived?

609
00:45:57.509 --> 00:45:59.241
Is he interested in me?

610
00:46:01.765 --> 00:46:04.823
Oh... hello.

611
00:46:12.372 --> 00:46:13.910
Do you want to eat this?

612
00:46:13.910 --> 00:46:14.984
What?

613
00:46:17.460 --> 00:46:20.341
You didn't have to buy me this.

614
00:46:24.993 --> 00:46:26.763
Uh... excuse me.

615
00:46:31.759 --> 00:46:34.172
What is this? I'm so popular.

616
00:47:18.578 --> 00:47:21.002
What? You didn't quit?

617
00:47:21.002 --> 00:47:23.143
Why would I quit?

618
00:47:23.143 --> 00:47:26.002
I was a bit sick yesterday,
so I went to the hospital.

619
00:47:26.002 --> 00:47:28.654
Stop being so tough.
That's enough now.

620
00:47:28.654 --> 00:47:31.247
I'll pay you for the work you did so far.

621
00:47:31.247 --> 00:47:33.754
Just quit already.

622
00:47:33.754 --> 00:47:36.038
Sorry, but I can't do that.

623
00:47:36.038 --> 00:47:38.649
I told you that you couldn't
leave work while on the job.

624
00:47:38.649 --> 00:47:41.645
It wasn't leaving on the job.
I had to go to the hospital.

625
00:47:41.645 --> 00:47:43.145
That's your own personal problem.

626
00:47:43.145 --> 00:47:45.326
You should quit
if you're too sick to work.

627
00:47:45.326 --> 00:47:47.346
Don't be a nuisance to everyone.

628
00:47:48.830 --> 00:47:51.919
Manager, you're being too harsh.

629
00:47:51.919 --> 00:47:54.091
You're the one who is too harsh.

630
00:47:54.091 --> 00:47:56.560
What are you planning
by staying around like this?

631
00:47:56.560 --> 00:47:58.980
If you faint while on the job

632
00:47:58.980 --> 00:48:01.821
are you going to ask
for worker's compensation?

633
00:48:01.821 --> 00:48:03.509
Ah.

634
00:48:03.509 --> 00:48:06.848
Is that what you are after?

635
00:48:08.837 --> 00:48:10.614
That man.

636
00:48:10.614 --> 00:48:12.422
Whether you faint here or not

637
00:48:12.422 --> 00:48:16.279
neither Gangsu Group nor
Hangang Services hold any responsibility.

638
00:48:16.279 --> 00:48:18.538
Quit now if you understand that.

639
00:48:18.538 --> 00:48:20.848
Manager, you're out of line.

640
00:48:20.848 --> 00:48:23.089
What are you talking about?

641
00:48:23.089 --> 00:48:25.689
Mister Kim, do you want to get fired too?

642
00:48:25.689 --> 00:48:27.422
- Seriously?
- What nonsense.

643
00:48:27.422 --> 00:48:29.230
- How ridiculous.
- Is he for real?

644
00:48:29.230 --> 00:48:31.152
- He's the worst.
- For sure.

645
00:48:31.152 --> 00:48:32.978
He has some nerve.

646
00:48:34.337 --> 00:48:35.489
What's with you all?

647
00:48:35.489 --> 00:48:37.323
All of you go to work now!

648
00:48:38.359 --> 00:48:40.656
Seriously now.

649
00:48:40.656 --> 00:48:44.205
Oh, look at the lot of you.

650
00:48:44.205 --> 00:48:46.926
Do all of you want
to get fired? Is that it?

651
00:48:46.926 --> 00:48:49.285
Manager, do you want to get fired?

652
00:48:49.285 --> 00:48:51.091
- Huh?
- What... what?

653
00:48:51.091 --> 00:48:53.404
- Mister Lee.
- Stay put!

654
00:48:53.404 --> 00:48:57.475
If we don't work now and
just leave, what can you do about it?

655
00:48:57.475 --> 00:48:59.406
They will say the cleaning job is a mess.

656
00:48:59.406 --> 00:49:01.622
The company employees
will complain loudly.

657
00:49:01.622 --> 00:49:04.852
If you don't empty trash for half a day,
the place is overflowing with it.

658
00:49:04.852 --> 00:49:06.687
Can you re-sign
the contract, at that rate?

659
00:49:06.687 --> 00:49:10.165
- That's right.
- No, you can't!

660
00:49:10.165 --> 00:49:11.305
Of course.

661
00:49:11.305 --> 00:49:13.346
Are you threatening me?

662
00:49:13.346 --> 00:49:15.683
You're the one making
threats, Manager Jung.

663
00:49:15.683 --> 00:49:18.810
- When did I do that?
- You just did!

664
00:49:18.810 --> 00:49:20.167
Why you people...

665
00:49:20.167 --> 00:49:22.335
Are going to take
an organized group action?

666
00:49:22.335 --> 00:49:25.031
Should we? Should we, Manager Jung?

667
00:49:25.031 --> 00:49:27.498
- Yes.
- Let's do it.

668
00:49:27.498 --> 00:49:29.636
- Let's go for it!
- Come on.

669
00:49:32.069 --> 00:49:34.058
Act like a manager if you're the manager.

670
00:49:34.058 --> 00:49:35.825
You think you're all that if
you're manager?

671
00:49:38.980 --> 00:49:41.285
What? An organized group action?

672
00:49:41.285 --> 00:49:44.705
Yes, they've gone mad
because of that girl Baek Joon.

673
00:49:44.705 --> 00:49:46.395
They all refuse to work.

674
00:49:46.395 --> 00:49:48.399
<i>They all suddenly got up and left.</i>

675
00:49:50.319 --> 00:49:52.149
What the heck is that?

676
00:49:53.629 --> 00:49:55.498
Good morning, CEO Min.

677
00:49:55.498 --> 00:49:59.080
- Seriously, this punk.
- What?

678
00:49:59.080 --> 00:50:02.234
Excuse me? Me?

679
00:50:02.234 --> 00:50:04.353
Are you talking to me?

680
00:50:04.353 --> 00:50:05.743
Let's talk later.

681
00:50:09.064 --> 00:50:10.172
What's with you?

682
00:50:10.172 --> 00:50:12.113
I came to see you, CEO Min.

683
00:50:12.113 --> 00:50:13.843
Your door happened to be open.

684
00:50:16.593 --> 00:50:17.973
What's your business with me?

685
00:50:19.024 --> 00:50:22.823
I just had one thing
I wanted you to know.

686
00:50:22.823 --> 00:50:23.940
What?

687
00:50:31.002 --> 00:50:35.872
You won't be able to renew your
contract with Gangsu Group.

688
00:50:35.872 --> 00:50:36.892
What?

689
00:50:36.892 --> 00:50:38.792
I'll stop you from
renewing that contract.

690
00:50:41.114 --> 00:50:45.776
Gosh... what are going on about so
early in the morning, you punk?

691
00:50:45.776 --> 00:50:50.466
Hey, you've been tossed out by your
family, so how will you stop it?

692
00:50:50.466 --> 00:50:52.576
You're dressed in this cleaner's uniform.

693
00:50:52.576 --> 00:50:55.451
You picked up money
from construction. What can you do?

694
00:50:55.451 --> 00:50:58.241
Then who are trusting
to act so foolishly?

695
00:51:00.741 --> 00:51:03.852
Your older brother
told me to stomp you out.

696
00:51:03.852 --> 00:51:04.892
Satisfied?

697
00:51:08.837 --> 00:51:12.140
Do you think you can handle it?

698
00:51:14.955 --> 00:51:17.038
I'll have to handle it.

699
00:51:17.038 --> 00:51:18.091
What can I do about it?

700
00:51:19.457 --> 00:51:20.526
What?

701
00:51:32.256 --> 00:51:34.640
He'll handle it.

702
00:51:34.640 --> 00:51:36.248
Hyuk said that?

703
00:51:36.248 --> 00:51:37.917
Yes.

704
00:51:37.917 --> 00:51:40.426
There is a problem in the building
management, as well.

705
00:51:40.426 --> 00:51:44.707
Byun Hyuk and someone else, Baek Joon,
have mobilized my company employees.

706
00:51:44.707 --> 00:51:46.968
They are taking a group action.

707
00:51:46.968 --> 00:51:49.973
The plan on protesting during
the sampling event tomorrow.

708
00:51:49.973 --> 00:51:52.312
What should I do?

709
00:51:52.312 --> 00:51:57.254
Should I take care
of it before it gets noisy?

710
00:51:57.254 --> 00:51:58.830
No.

711
00:51:58.830 --> 00:51:59.991
Excuse me?

712
00:52:02.841 --> 00:52:04.473
Leave them alone.

713
00:52:08.535 --> 00:52:10.745
What do you mean?

714
00:52:10.745 --> 00:52:13.444
It seems like Hyuk
is determined for once.

715
00:52:13.444 --> 00:52:16.955
Leave him and let's see what he does.

716
00:52:16.955 --> 00:52:21.174
But, the CEO will be at
the sampling event tomorrow.

717
00:52:21.174 --> 00:52:23.935
Not just the CEO,
but external parties too.

718
00:52:23.935 --> 00:52:26.457
There will be reporters with cameras.

719
00:52:26.457 --> 00:52:27.620
Will it be okay?

720
00:52:29.730 --> 00:52:31.928
Hyuk says he will handle it.

721
00:52:35.440 --> 00:52:37.727
Leave him alone to do what he wants.

722
00:52:38.928 --> 00:52:42.127
The event will be ruined and
Hyuk will be taken care of.

723
00:52:42.127 --> 00:52:44.187
Two birds with one stone, right?

724
00:52:53.027 --> 00:52:55.069
Just pretend you didn't know.

725
00:52:55.069 --> 00:52:59.218
Since Hyuk will cause the problem,
you won't get in trouble.

726
00:53:08.690 --> 00:53:11.803
Where have you been
all this time? The event is tomorrow.

727
00:53:11.803 --> 00:53:14.674
Will the event run smoothly?

728
00:53:14.674 --> 00:53:16.105
I'm sorry.

729
00:53:16.105 --> 00:53:18.165
I'm sure he'll do well.

730
00:53:18.165 --> 00:53:20.603
He has great personnel record.

731
00:53:20.603 --> 00:53:24.464
All of the projects he's
taken on have succeeded.

732
00:53:24.464 --> 00:53:29.305
Also, he wouldn't mess up
the first event he takes on here.

733
00:53:29.305 --> 00:53:30.424
Isn't that right?

734
00:53:32.730 --> 00:53:34.844
I will do my best, Director.

735
00:53:35.846 --> 00:53:37.212
You will have to.

736
00:53:38.442 --> 00:53:39.835
I'm looking forward to tomorrow.

737
00:53:43.582 --> 00:53:45.457
Hey.

738
00:53:45.457 --> 00:53:49.926
You know how important this event is
to the Managing Director and team, right?

739
00:53:49.926 --> 00:53:52.225
There had better not be any problems.

740
00:54:03.636 --> 00:54:05.165
Come on. Hurry.

741
00:54:05.165 --> 00:54:07.783
- Everyone's here.
- Come on.

742
00:54:07.783 --> 00:54:10.303
Hurry. Gather around.

743
00:54:10.303 --> 00:54:13.969
I'm going to go all the way this time.

744
00:54:15.451 --> 00:54:17.875
<i>[Eliminate Temporary Employment]</i>

745
00:54:21.529 --> 00:54:22.634
Here you go.

746
00:54:22.634 --> 00:54:23.810
Thanks.

747
00:54:23.810 --> 00:54:25.562
Let's go now.

748
00:54:25.562 --> 00:54:27.085
All right.

749
00:54:27.085 --> 00:54:28.406
Let's go.

750
00:54:28.406 --> 00:54:29.801
Hold on.

751
00:54:29.801 --> 00:54:32.971
You really don't have to do this.

752
00:54:32.971 --> 00:54:35.415
Are cleaning employees not human?

753
00:54:35.415 --> 00:54:38.767
Does it make sense that we
can't even get worker's compensation?

754
00:54:38.767 --> 00:54:43.256
This happened because you fought
to get us cafeteria meal tickets.

755
00:54:43.256 --> 00:54:45.290
We wouldn't be humans
if we ignored that.

756
00:54:45.290 --> 00:54:46.694
Yes, of course.

757
00:54:46.694 --> 00:54:49.886
It's time for their contract
renewal, so they can't ignore us.

758
00:54:49.886 --> 00:54:52.993
If we don't speak up now,
they won't blink an eye.

759
00:54:52.993 --> 00:54:54.915
Yes, that's right.

760
00:54:54.915 --> 00:54:56.294
That's for certain.

761
00:54:56.294 --> 00:54:58.060
Wait, wait.

762
00:54:58.060 --> 00:55:01.857
I'm very grateful that you are all
feeling the heartache and anger with me.

763
00:55:01.857 --> 00:55:03.821
Still, you don't have to do this.

764
00:55:03.821 --> 00:55:06.776
It's okay if I get fired,
but what if you all get fired?

765
00:55:06.776 --> 00:55:09.823
Joon, what happened to you...

766
00:55:09.823 --> 00:55:13.000
it could happen to
any of us at any time.

767
00:55:13.000 --> 00:55:17.176
This isn't because of you,
so don't feel that way.

768
00:55:17.176 --> 00:55:18.187
Mister Kim.

769
00:55:18.187 --> 00:55:20.462
I'll quit if they want to fire me.

770
00:55:20.462 --> 00:55:22.562
I can find another job like this.

771
00:55:22.562 --> 00:55:25.558
If you step on me,
I may not be able to wiggle a lot

772
00:55:25.558 --> 00:55:28.201
but I will move about a bit if I can!

773
00:55:28.201 --> 00:55:29.790
- Sounds good!
- Yes.

774
00:55:30.955 --> 00:55:32.638
Let's go now!

775
00:55:32.638 --> 00:55:34.571
We need to show them!

776
00:55:34.571 --> 00:55:35.895
You're all right.

777
00:55:38.848 --> 00:55:41.038
We need to show them.

778
00:55:41.038 --> 00:55:42.457
Hyuk.

779
00:55:42.457 --> 00:55:47.908
But, this method... it's so old.

780
00:55:47.908 --> 00:55:51.473
As you all know,
I personally know the CEO.

781
00:55:51.473 --> 00:55:55.578
A strike isn't the kind of thing
that will work on him.

782
00:55:55.578 --> 00:55:58.629
Really? Then what will work?

783
00:56:00.696 --> 00:56:02.098
A show.

784
00:56:02.098 --> 00:56:05.006
- A show?
